Bugs Fixed
Bug 1 — Silent contact skip for campaigns > 50 contacts (campaign.worker.ts)
The worker was doing findMany({ where: { status: "QUEUED" }, skip: batchOffset, take: 50 }). After batch 1 processes 50 contacts (they become SENT), the next job runs with skip: 50 — but there are only the remaining QUEUED contacts left to skip, so it skips them all and marks the campaign complete. Everyone after contact #50 was silently dropped.

Fix: removed skip entirely. Each batch always fetches the first N QUEUED contacts by createdAt order.

Bug 2 — Delivered/Read/Failed always shows 0% (webhook.worker.ts)
Webhook callbacks from Meta updated individual CampaignContact.status rows but never rolled up into Campaign.deliveredCount / readCount / failedCount. Now after each status update the worker does a groupBy and writes accurate counts to the campaign.

Bug 3 — Error column always blank (webhook.worker.ts)
Meta's failure reason was in updateData.errorMessage but was never written to CampaignContact. Now saved. You'll see the exact error (e.g. "The number is not registered on WhatsApp") in the campaign detail table.

Why one of your 2 contacts wasn't received
Both API calls returned HTTP 200 (Meta accepted them), so sentCount = 2. The actual delivery failure arrives later via a webhook — Meta sends status: "failed" with an error like code 131026 ("number not on WhatsApp"). Since webhooks weren't configured, that failure was invisible. After the fixes above, once webhooks are working, you'll see:

The failed contact in the campaign detail table with the error reason
Delivered % will reflect real delivery
How to connect Meta Webhooks
Step 1 — Get your webhook URL and verify token
Your webhook URL is already generated and stored. Run this on your server to get it:


SELECT "phoneNumberId", "webhookVerifyToken" FROM "WhatsAppNumber";
Your webhook URL is:


https://wazenly.homestudy.online/api/webhooks/meta/{phoneNumberId}
Step 2 — Configure in Meta Developer Console
Go to developers.facebook.com → your app → WhatsApp → Configuration
Under Webhook, click Edit
Callback URL: https://wazenly.homestudy.online/api/webhooks/meta/{your_phoneNumberId}
Verify token: the value from webhookVerifyToken in your DB
Click Verify and Save
Step 3 — Subscribe to webhook fields
After verification, subscribe to these fields:

messages — incoming messages to your inbox
message_deliveries — delivery confirmations
message_reads — read receipts
message_template_status_update — template approvals
Step 4 — Verify it works
Send a test message. Within seconds you should see:

Delivered % update in the campaign detail
Incoming replies appear in your Inbox
Failed deliveries show the error reason in the contact table
Note: Your code at numbers.ts:70 already tries to auto-register the webhook when a number is added, but it silently fails if the access token doesn't have the whatsapp_business_management permission. If auto-registration failed, follow the manual steps above.